      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 2040: 🟡 Messages for which plugins produce no bodyOverwrite are never marked as processed. Because loadMissingBodyOverwrites() is called after every loadConversation/loadSwarmUntil, the same messages will be retransformed on every history load, which can become very expensive for large conversations or network-backed plugins. Store an explicit local processed state, or cache negative results separately from the user-visible pluginData field so unchanged messages are skipped on subsequent loads.",
