      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2148: 🔴 updateMessageBodyOverwrite() accepts and stores arbitrary overwrite text without validating the target message kind or bounding the payload size. A plugin can attach large data to any cached commit, including non-text commits, causing unnecessary memory growth and large SwarmMessageUpdated emissions. Validate that the target is a text message or text edition, reject reactions/non-text commits, and cap bodyOverwrite to the same practical limit used for message bodies before storing it.",
