      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2259: 🔴 The loaded messages are emitted before plugin body overwrites are computed, even though the new ChatHandler API documents that transformation happens before SwarmLoaded. Clients will first render stale/untranslated bodies and then receive a burst of SwarmMessageUpdated signals, which can cause flicker and makes clients that only consume SwarmLoaded miss the overwrite data. Compute/inject overwrites before emitting SwarmLoaded, or update the loaded message vector before the signal. Suggested direction:\n```suggestion\nif (auto convPtr \u003d convWeak.lock())\n    convPtr-\u003eloadMissingBodyOverwrites();\nemitSignal\u003clibjami::ConversationSignal::SwarmLoaded\u003e(id, accountId, conversationId, messages);\n```",
